A new cancer vaccine can teach the immune system to "see" cells with abnormal behaviour
A new cancer vaccine can teach the immune system to "see" cells with abnormal behaviour and kill them.
The vaccine teaches the immune system to recognise cells with abnormal behavior as part of treatment.
The method involves extracting the immune cells from a patient, which are transformed into a laboratory.
